After the rain and cold temperatures of Dublin proved to be too much for our summer vacation, we decided to take a short trip to Rome and booked the Cicerone last minute for an excellent price.	We stayed afterwards at the Milton Roma which was also 4-star but a much better price, better standard (flat screen tvs, brand new, great breakfast) and a higher league of satisfaction and service.	This is a 4 star hotel on the North Side of the river, about 10 minutes walk from Vatican City We paid 310€ for 3 nights (for 2 people) incl breakfast and we couldnt really fault the value.